The President praises the efforts of Democrats in the House to bring immigration reform to a vote, while criticizing Republicans in the House for refusing to do so. He emphasizes that immigration reform would strengthen borders, modernize the legal immigration system, and keep families together. The President also highlights the economic benefits of reform, stating that it would reduce deficits by $900 billion over the next 20 years. He argues that immigration reform is necessary for the economy, security, and future of the country, and expresses gratitude to congressional leaders who are working towards progress.